-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

TO START THE GAME YOU MUST EXECUTE THE startup-sequence. (or Boot the disk)

If you install X-BALLS in your DH0: or similar, just be sure that the 
directory LEVELS/ is located immediatly inside the SYS: (Eg.: DH0:LEVELS/).

I was tired of waiting X-BALLS to load brushes and sounds from DF0: 
( yes ! I have got only that drive..! I feel ashame ! )
so I archived the game and it's files (not the LEVELS) into the single 
XBALLS.LHA file.

The startup-sequence extracts the files into RAM: and X_BALLS(the executable)
loads and then deletes them from there.
I did this becouse the loading results much faster this way.

