THE GAME.....

Ok. For some strange and inaxplicable reason, your mission is to build
circuits to steer two gummy XBALLS into a PROTO-BOX (P.B.).
You are working in a futuristic and coloured artificial area,and all you
need is your mouse.
You can access the KIT-PANEL by pressing the left mouse button.
Here you may select DIFFERENT-SHAPED-BLOCKS (D.S.B.) to build the circuit 
for the Xballs. BUT ! You may need some SPECIAL-ANIMATED-BLOCKS (S.A.B.)
which are activated whenever a Xball is close enough to them.
A big number of D.S.B. is allowed in each level.
The trouble is you may not use more then 5 S.A.B. in each level, and you
ought to drive the XBALLS into the P.B.  before timer reaches 00 .
XBALLS bounce on obstacles and feel the effects of gravity.
Selection of D.S.B. or S.A.B. may be done moving the ARTIFICIAL-ARM (A.A.) on
the desired BLOCK and clicking the LEFT-MOUSE-BUTTON(L.M.B.)(i'm going nuts!)
To exit from track-editing and from the KIT-PANEL, click the right mouse b.

Just remember: left  mouseb. = enter or select.
	       right mouseb. = return back.
	       ESC = restart game.	

	! For each level passed, a password will be displayed !
(I hate games which force you to start EVERYTHING over again and again...)

